				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.osopinion.com/perl/story/12799.html&quot;&gt;Bert Garcia&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;Who uses all the applications in the MS Office suite? In a small business of let's say 15 employees, maybe 10 have to type up a letter, two do occasional spreadsheets, one brave salesperson attempts a presentation and none want to tackle a database. Seems like a waste of disk space, not to mention license fees.&quot; &lt;i&gt;Good point.&lt;/i&gt;"/>
				<outline text="Dan Gillmor: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.siliconvalley.com/docs/opinion/dgillmor/dg081501.htm&quot;&gt;Big Blue places $1 billion bet on Linux&lt;/a&gt;."/>
				<outline text="Today is &lt;a href=&quot;http://scobleizer.manilasites.com/&quot;&gt;Scoble's&lt;/a&gt; first day as a UserLander. &lt;i&gt;Welcome!&lt;/i&gt;"/>
				<outline text="It's confirmed. The correct pronunciation of Mitch Kapor's last name is, as I thought, &lt;i&gt;Kay&lt;/i&gt;-pour not Kuh-&lt;i&gt;pour.&lt;/i&gt;"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.creativityworkshop.com/florence.html&quot;&gt;Florence&lt;/a&gt; must be a great place for a creativity workshop."/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://jogger.jabber.org/&quot;&gt;Jogger&lt;/a&gt; is a Jabber-powered weblog system. Let's get this working through Manila and Blogger too."/>
				<outline text="Giles Turnbull: &lt;a href=&quot;http://writetheweb.com/read.php?item=114&quot;&gt;A new direction for weblogs -- pornography&lt;/a&gt;."/>
				<outline text="Sometimes I can't believe the words that are &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.dictionary.com/cgi-bin/dict.pl?term=dingleberry&quot;&gt;defined&lt;/a&gt; on dictionary.com. Great job, whoever's doing it."/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://davenet.userland.com/1997/02/09/BreakingRules&quot;&gt;2/9/97&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;Listening is still a precious commodity. Nothing's changed there. If you want to make a contribution to making the world a better place, please listen to someone today, tomorrow -- every day. Have the courage to let them exceed your expectations.&quot; (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/davenet/97/review/life.html&quot;&gt;More&lt;/a&gt; 1997 life quotes.)"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.xml.com/pub/a/2001/08/15/taglines.html&quot;&gt;Edd Dumbill&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;Perhaps some of the uneasiness is due to the fact that web services proponents have never demonstrated how to do any more than retrieve a stock quote.&quot; "/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://wmf.editthispage.com/discuss/msgReader$5125?mode=day&quot;&gt;Jeremy Bowers&lt;/a&gt; did a fact-sheet on the DMCA. &lt;i&gt;Thanks!&lt;/i&gt;"/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://msl1.mit.edu/ESD10/sslinks/&quot;&gt;Frank Field&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;I have a bunch of stuff on DMCA, from a variety of sources, that my be useful.&quot;"/>
				<outline text="Yesterday I took a nasty fall getting into the hot tub. Bruised my side, totally sore this morning. Had a scary thought. In twenty years that's going to be a broken hip. Better go out and get some of those bathtub traction creator thingies. "/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://lyrics.rockmagic.net/lyrics/cooper_alice/love_it_to_death_1971.html#im_eighteen_3_00&quot;&gt;Alice Cooper&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;I got a baby's brain and an old man's heart. Took eighteen years to get this far.&quot;"/>
				<outline text="&lt;rules&gt;">
					<outline text="&lt;rule level=&quot;1&quot; to=&quot;1&quot;&gt;">
						<outline text="&lt;textStyle&gt;bold&lt;/textStyle&gt;"/>
